( '129', '50', 'How do I start writing coursework?', '<p><span id="docs-internal-guid-eae1b75a-7fff-23fc-cb35-86ae4fda2975"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;">Writing coursework involves four main steps - Research, planning, drafting, and making edits. It is a lengthy process which may take time to complete. Students will have to research the coursework and extract every possible useful information they get. Next, they must create an outline based on the research and follow it up by drafting the content. Alternatively, students can also hire a professional coursework writer and get the job done easily.</span></span><br></p>', '2024-05-11 06:01:22', '2024-05-11 06:01:22' ),
